festival.introText:
Rebellion Festivals is the largest independent Punk / Alternative music festival in the world. Over 4 days every August in Blackpool, the very best in Punk gather for the social event of the year. Many revelers treat the festival as a main holiday and go every year. The 4000 attendees say there is a very familiar feel to the weekend and that 'it's like one big family.'

All forms of punk are represented with Anarcho bands playing alongside '77 Punks groups on the same bill as Oi bands sharing the same stage as UK82 style bands who are appearing with Street Punk outfits next to the new breed of young punk bands coming through. There is also an acoustic stage and an alternative stage 'Bizarre Bazaar' which has comedy, burlesque dancing and a variety of other entertainment - most notably Punk Rock Bingo!

artists.name: Pete Bentham and the Dinner Ladies

faqs.question: When is Rebellion 2023?
faqs.answer: Rebellion takes place Thursday 3rd August - Sunday 6th August 2023.

faqs.question: How to get to Rebellion
faqs.answer: The nearest major cities to Blackpool are Manchester and Liverpool and there are regular train services to and from Blackpool at both.

faqs.question: Accessibility information
faqs.answer: You can read Rebellion's statement on accessibility here: https://www.rebellionfestivals.com/accessibility

faqs.question: Is there camping available at Rebellion Festival?
faqs.answer: No, Rebellion takes place in the centre of Blackpool so there is no camping available, however there are plenty of hotels, bed & breakfasts, and guest houses close by.

faqs.question: Where is Rebellion?
faqs.answer: Rebellion is located at The Winter Gardens, Church Street, Blackpool, Lancashire, FY1 1HL.

faqs.question: Are there any age restrictions at Rebellion?
faqs.answer: No, Rebellion is an all-ages event. Children under 12 are free with an adult holding a weekend ticket (maximum 3 children per adult) and must be accompanied by an adult at all times. If your child is under 12 but looks older than you may be asked to provide proof of age ID for free entry.

faqs.question: Is Rebellion inside or outside?
faqs.answer: Rebellion is an indoor festival in Blackpool Winter Gardens.

faqs.question: What time do the doors open at Rebellion?
faqs.answer: Doors open at 11am on THURSDAY and 12pm on FRIDAY / SATURDAY / SUNDAY.

location.address: The Winter Gardens, 97 Church Street, Blackpool
